### 7. BachelorŌĆÖs thesis ŌĆö 12 LP

The thesis component, including presentation, carries **12 LP**.

Admission requires:

- at least **90 successfully completed LP**;
- successful completion of **Wissenschaftliches Arbeiten in der Informatik, 6 LP**;
- the student must most recently have been enrolled in the FU Berlin B.Sc. Informatik programme. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn260886view3Ņłü

Binding thesis conditions:

- Topic must be from Informatik.
- Processing time: **12 weeks**.
- Expected length: approximately **7,500 words**.
- Language: German or English; another language requires approval.
- The topic may be returned once within the first four weeks.
- Electronic submission is required.
- Results must be presented and discussed orally: approximately **15 minutes presentation plus 15 minutes discussion**.
- The presentation is part of the 12-LP thesis component but is not separately graded.
- The written thesis must receive at least **4.0** to pass. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn260886view4Ņłéturn236184view2Ņłü

## Older regulation and transition rules

The **2014 StO/PO, codes 0086c/0086d**, is no longer the current regulation for newly enrolled students. It remains relevant only to students enrolled before the 2023 regulation took effect who have not switched to the new rules. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn607404view2Ņłéturn260886view5Ņłü

For those students:

- They may apply to switch to the 2023 regulation.
- The examination board determines how previously completed or commenced modules are transferred.
- The switch becomes effective at the beginning of the lecture period of the following semester.
- The switch is **irreversible**.
- Completion under the 2014 regulation is guaranteed only until the **end of Summer Semester 2027**. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn260886view5Ņłéturn607404view3Ņłü

Thus, the 2014 requirementsŌĆösuch as its older Pflicht-, Vertiefungs- and Anwendungsbereich structureŌĆömust not be mixed with the 2023 requirements unless the student is formally still governed by that older regulation.

